					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm envisioning a tool, somewhat like <a href="http://www.openscad.org/" class="postlink">openscad</a> for 3d design, where a text-based editor lives right beside some sort of GUI tools for previewing and interacting with the output.  <br /><br />I'm not much of a composer, but for something like famitracker, it's not the input format that I find to be that useful (being relatively inexperienced, I find the input system on famitracker to be every bit as cumbersome as text), but instead the advantage is the ability to instantly preview what I did. Like others are saying, it's all about things like muting/soloing, replaying small bits or a single line, etc.  If you gave me a text interface to compose, but with full-featured gui tools for listening to it in lots of different ways (integrated in such a way that there wasn't a separate export/compile step to slow things down), I'd be happy.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />My games: <a href="http://www.bitethechili.com" class="postlink">http://www.bitethechili.com</a></div>
